# basketball-scouting environment variables
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values for
# anything you need locally. Scripts read these via `scripts/config.py`.
#
# `.env` is NOT auto-loaded — Python doesn't read it by default. Either:
#   PowerShell:  $env:FIRECRAWL_API_KEY = "fc-..."
#   bash:        export FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=fc-...
# or use a tool like `python-dotenv` if you want auto-loading.

# --- Path overrides --------------------------------------------------------
# Leave unset to use the defaults (everything relative to the repo root).
# Set BBSCOUT_ROOT to relocate the whole tree at once (useful for tests,
# containers, or running scripts against a fixture copy).
#
# BBSCOUT_ROOT=/path/to/basketball-scouting
#
# Per-directory overrides only matter when one subtree lives somewhere
# different from the rest. Almost no one needs these.
#
# BBSCOUT_SCRIPTS_DIR=
# BBSCOUT_RAW_DIR=
# BBSCOUT_OUTPUT_DIR=
# BBSCOUT_WIKI_DIR=
# BBSCOUT_DOCS_DIR=
# BBSCOUT_PUBLISHED_DIR=
# BBSCOUT_AUDITS_DIR=

# --- Secrets ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Firecrawl is the scraping service used by the experimental research-packet
# pipeline (scripts/firecrawl_qual_test.py and scripts/experiments/firecrawl/).
# Get a key at https://www.firecrawl.dev/. Required only when running those
# scripts; the core domain stat pipeline does not need it.
#
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=fc-...
